  {
    "id": "kp-2.6-01",
    "section": "2.6",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Simultaneous Linear Equations",
    "title_zh": "联立一次方程组",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "**Simultaneous equations** are a set of equations with multiple variables that are all true at the same time.\n\n**Elimination Method:** Multiply one or both equations by numbers so that the coefficients of one variable are the same (or opposite). Then add or subtract the equations to eliminate that variable.\n\n**Substitution Method:** Rearrange one equation to express one variable in terms of the other, then substitute this into the second equation.",
      "zh": "**联立方程组**是指一组包含多个变量且同时成立的方程。\n\n**消元法：** 将其中一个或两个方程乘以某个数，使其中一个变量的系数相同（或互为相反数）。然后通过加减方程来消去该变量。\n\n**代入法：** 改写其中一个方程，用一个变量表示另一个变量，然后将其代入第二个方程中。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-solve-simultaneous",
        "label": "Solve simultaneous equations",
        "label_zh": "解联立方程组",
        "description": "Find the values of $x$ and $y$ that satisfy both linear equations.",
        "description_zh": "找出同时满足两个一次方程的 $x$ 和 $y$ 的值。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-solve-simultaneous",
        "question": "Solve the simultaneous equations:\n$3x + 2y = 12$\n$x + y = 5$",
        "question_zh": "解联立方程组：\n$3x + 2y = 12$\n$x + y = 5$",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Multiply the second equation by 2 to match the $y$ coefficients.\n$2x + 2y = 10$\n\n**Step 2:** Subtract this from the first equation.\n$(3x + 2y) - (2x + 2y) = 12 - 10$\n$x = 2$\n\n**Step 3:** Substitute $x = 2$ back into the simplest equation ($x + y = 5$).\n$2 + y = 5 \\Rightarrow y = 3$\n\n**Answer:** $x = 2, y = 3$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 将第二个方程乘以 2，使 $y$ 的系数匹配。\n$2x + 2y = 10$\n\n**步骤2：** 用第一个方程减去这个新方程。\n$(3x + 2y) - (2x + 2y) = 12 - 10$\n$x = 2$\n\n**步骤3：** 将 $x = 2$ 代回最简单的方程（$x + y = 5$）。\n$2 + y = 5 \\Rightarrow y = 3$\n\n**答案：** $x = 2, y = 3$",
        "source": "Adapted from 4MA1/2F/June/2018"
      },
      {
        "patternId": "ep-solve-simultaneous",
        "question": "Solve:\n$5x - 2y = 19$\n$3x + 4y = 1$",
        "question_zh": "解方程组：\n$5x - 2y = 19$\n$3x + 4y = 1$",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Multiply the first equation by 2.\n$10x - 4y = 38$\n\n**Step 2:** Add the equations to eliminate $y$ (since signs are different).\n$(10x - 4y) + (3x + 4y) = 38 + 1$\n$13x = 39 \\Rightarrow x = 3$\n\n**Step 3:** Substitute $x = 3$ into $3x + 4y = 1$.\n$3(3) + 4y = 1 \\Rightarrow 9 + 4y = 1$\n$4y = -8 \\Rightarrow y = -2$\n\n**Answer:** $x = 3, y = -2$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 将第一个方程乘以 2。\n$10x - 4y = 38$\n\n**步骤2：** 将两个方程相加消去 $y$（因为符号相反）。\n$(10x - 4y) + (3x + 4y) = 38 + 1$\n$13x = 39 \\Rightarrow x = 3$\n\n**步骤3：** 将 $x = 3$ 代入 $3x + 4y = 1$。\n$3(3) + 4y = 1 \\Rightarrow 9 + 4y = 1$\n$4y = -8 \\Rightarrow y = -2$\n\n**答案：** $x = 3, y = -2$",
        "source": "Adapted from 4MA1/1H/Jan/2020"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
